this is a really great capability

00:05:30.700 --> 00:05:31.840
inside of iTunes Connect.

00:05:31.840 --> 00:05:38.060
And we'll show you how this works today
in the noon App Store marketing session.

00:05:38.080 --> 00:05:42.800
Another thing that we heard from
developers and that we were able

00:05:42.800 --> 00:05:47.070
to implement is over-the-air
download limit changes.

00:05:47.080 --> 00:05:51.560
So the limit was raised from
50 megabytes to 100 megabytes,

00:05:51.560 --> 00:05:55.180
and this makes it easier for people to
get your games when they're on the go.

00:05:55.200 --> 00:05:57.190
Even if they're not on Wi-Fi.

00:05:57.200 --> 00:06:00.420
And this is huge for
you as game developers,

00:06:00.420 --> 00:06:01.200
right?

00:06:01.230 --> 00:06:04.120
Because many of you were doing a
lot of work to keep your binary

00:06:04.120 --> 00:06:06.200
sizes down to about 50 megabytes.

00:06:06.400 --> 00:06:10.200
And you were trying to
keep under that ceiling.

00:06:10.410 --> 00:06:15.200
And so this change means that it's a lot
easier for you to build a universal app,

00:06:15.200 --> 00:06:18.200
to include your retina assets,
to include a 64-bit slice,

00:06:18.200 --> 00:06:23.330
and all the other things that
you need to put into your binary.

00:06:24.000 --> 00:06:28.220
Now, the other thing we did was we heard
a lot of feedback from developers who

00:06:28.270 --> 00:06:30.620
