important one for us.

00:10:40.560 --> 00:10:46.530
We saw a fundamental evolution in
the iOS operating system on the

00:10:46.530 --> 00:10:50.280
platform with the release of iOS 7.

00:10:50.280 --> 00:10:54.090
And we introduced a whole
bunch of new devices.

00:10:54.100 --> 00:10:59.420
And the thing to realize is that these
changes provide... a completely new

00:10:59.420 --> 00:11:05.760
basis for...or a new foundation for
a next generation of games and apps.

00:11:05.760 --> 00:11:08.390
And that's really what we
want to talk about today.

00:11:08.480 --> 00:11:12.540
So at WWDC, as you know,
we introduced iOS 7.

00:11:12.540 --> 00:11:15.970
And it's the next generation of iOS,
obviously.

00:11:16.200 --> 00:11:22.490
There have been six previous...six major
releases of iOS previously since 2008

00:11:22.530 --> 00:11:25.920
when the SDK first came out with iOS 2.

00:11:26.390 --> 00:11:29.190
And every time there's a new release,
we're... you know,

00:11:29.190 --> 00:11:32.280
there's always a new SDK with
tons of new technology for you to

00:11:32.280 --> 00:11:34.060
take advantage of in your games.

00:11:34.060 --> 00:11:38.850
And iOS 7 is the most significant
update to iOS since 2007.

00:11:39.250 --> 00:11:41.440
Even though there have been
these six previous releases,

00:11:41.590 --> 00:11:43.770
we made a ton of changes with iOS 7.

00:11:43.940 --> 00:11:46.540
And now, obviously,
with the numbers I shared earlier,

00:11:46.540 --> 00:11:50.110
you've got hundreds of millions
of customers... that are running

00:11:50.110 --> 00:11:52.450
iOS 7 on their devices now.

00:11:52.840 --> 00:11:57.630
And iOS 7 has so many new technologies
and features for you to take

00:11:57.630 --> 00:11:59.340
advantage of as a game developer.

00:11:59.340 --> 00:12:01.790
I mean, there's SpriteKit for 2D games.

00:12:01.830 --> 00:12:05.020
Developers have been asking for
something like SpriteKit for years,

00:12:05.070 --> 00:12:06.060
and now it's here.

00:12:06.710 --> 00:12:09.510
There's a new framework for
supporting game controllers.

00:12:09.640 --> 00:12:12.430
We announced that at WWDC and
actually had game controllers

00:12:12.500 --> 00:12:15.630
for people to play around with
in the labs at the conference.

00:12:15.660 --> 00:12:19.160
There are major enhancements
to existing frameworks,

00:12:19.160 --> 00:12:23.920
so OpenGL ES3 and Game Center have
dramatically enhanced capabilities,

00:12:24.020 --> 00:12:27.300
and we'll cover these in
sessions later on today.

00:12:27.300 --> 00:12:30.400
And then there's 64-bit,
which lets you tap into the

00:12:30.490 --> 00:12:32.640
performance of the A7 processor.

00:12:32.640 --> 00:12:36.290
So iOS 7 is a huge change.

00:12:36.620 --> 00:12:38.820
Huge step forward as an OS release.

00:12:38.900 --> 00:12:41.300
It introduces a brand
new user experience,

00:12:41.360 --> 00:12:44.170
which you've all experienced,
but it also introduces a ton

00:12:44.170 --> 00:12:48.330
of technologies for you to take
advantage of as a game developer.

00:12:48.340 --> 00:12:51.600
And so, really,
no matter what kind of game you develop,

00:12:51.600 --> 00:12:55.570
whether it's an arcade game,
a puzzle game, a racing game, or an RPG,

00:12:55.570 --> 00:12:59.680
there is a lot of capabilities in
iOS 7 for you to take advantage of.

00:13:01.970 --> 00:13:04.540
And on the hardware side,
we introduced a new

00:13:04.540 --> 00:13:06.790
generation of iOS devices.

00:13:07.060 --> 00:13:09.620
You know, this is the iPad
Mini with Retina display.

00:13:09.630 --> 00:13:13.420
The iPad Air came out,
and they were the most recent

00:13:13.540 --> 00:13:15.400
introductions to the hardware line.

00:13:16.330 --> 00:13:20.680
And these are incredibly powerful
new devices that are built on the A7

00:13:20.680 --> 00:13:23.400
chip with its 64-bit architecture.

00:13:23.400 --> 00:13:29.400
And alongside of that,
they've got the M7 motion coprocessor.

00:13:29.400 --> 00:13:34.750
So these are very significant devices.

00:13:36.370 --> 00:13:41.400
And with that, prior to that,
we announced the iPhone 5c and the 5s.

00:13:41.400 --> 00:13:44.400
And the 5s is incredibly powerful.

00:13:44.790 --> 00:13:45.400
I mean, undoubtedly, you've been playing
with it for a long time.

00:13:45.940 --> 00:13:48.180
And running your games, you know,
builds of your games on it.

00:13:48.180 --> 00:13:51.390
And the GPU on that device
is awesome for games.

00:13:51.400 --> 00:13:53.380
And the speed is amazing.

00:13:54.360 --> 00:13:58.170
And we think that, really,
the iPhone 5s is going to be the

00:13:58.170 --> 00:14:00.400
new baseline for a lot of games.

00:14:00.530 --> 00:14:03.410
This is an incredible device.

00:14:04.460 --> 00:14:09.930
And it's the combination of these
new devices with the A7 processor

00:14:09.970 --> 00:14:14.300
and the retina displays and all of
their hardware capabilities combined

00:14:14.300 --> 00:14:20.300
with iOS 7 that form a foundation
for the next generation of iOS games.

00:14:21.390 --> 00:14:25.610
And helping you get the most
out of all of these technologies

00:14:25.610 --> 00:14:29.990
