people aren't going to do it for free.

00:15:00.720 --> 00:15:03.990
You can judge your game based on
the technologies that you adopt.

00:15:04.410 --> 00:15:05.500
It's not about the technologies.

00:15:06.280 --> 00:15:09.800
People don't buy games because
they use Game Center specifically.

00:15:10.650 --> 00:15:14.600
They don't buy games because
they're built on OpenGL ES 3 or 2.

00:15:14.750 --> 00:15:17.360
and they also, you know, great games.

00:15:17.410 --> 00:15:20.200
It's not about what API you
integrate specifically.

00:15:20.460 --> 00:15:22.890
It's not about the technology.

00:15:23.850 --> 00:15:26.800
Instead, what people want is
they want to have fun.

00:15:26.800 --> 00:15:28.510
They want to be entertained.

00:15:28.510 --> 00:15:32.310
They want to learn while they're
doing a logic puzzle or they want to,

00:15:32.310 --> 00:15:35.570
you know, a casual game or so,
or they want to be entertained

00:15:35.680 --> 00:15:38.880
in a group setting by doing
group gameplay over AirPlay.

00:15:38.880 --> 00:15:40.730
It's about being entertained.

00:15:40.730 --> 00:15:44.780
And so what's important to people who
are buying games is that the games are

00:15:44.850 --> 00:15:48.360
inviting and that they're engaging,
that they're intuitive,

00:15:48.440 --> 00:15:50.650
and that they're polished.

00:15:50.660 --> 00:15:53.870
And so let's talk about a
